<subSubSection lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1797,2038]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis: Characterized by unicolored dorsum, small and flat calli on anterior lobe of pronotum, slightly sinuate edges of pronotum and presence of teeth on the midtibiae of male.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1797,2038]" lastBlockId="73.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Redescription: Measurements, see Table VII. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[725,795,1869,1894]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Male:</emphasis>
Dorsal view: body oblong-oval. Antennae dark brown, base of exocorion and small dot on apex of cuneal fracture, paler. Pilosity semierect, sparse, not very long. Head: Eyes medium-sized; length of anteocular region subequal to eye length. Proportions of antennal segments (I:II:III:IV) 1: 3: 2.2: 2.3. Labium with segment II reaching midcoxae, III surpassing hind-coxae. Thorax: Pronotum slightly sinuate laterally, carina very marked on apical half; calli small, slightly protuberant, posterior margin slightly concave; collar thick; posterior lobe wrinkled (
<figureCitation box="[848,946,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–296" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetId="figure-252@72.[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 292–296. L. unicolor. Male. 292, Head and pronotum; 293, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) and pad (Fos); 294, Midtibia showing the row of teeth (Te); 295, Hemelytron showing the stub (Stu) in membranae; 296, Scheme of pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947977/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 292</figureCitation>
); hemelytra sinuate and not surpassing apex of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[312,417,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–296" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetId="figure-252@72.[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 292–296. L. unicolor. Male. 292, Head and pronotum; 293, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) and pad (Fos); 294, Midtibia showing the row of teeth (Te); 295, Hemelytron showing the stub (Stu) in membranae; 296, Scheme of pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947977/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 295</figureCitation>
); membrana from tip of cuneus subequal in length to cuneus. Ventrally dark brown, unicolored. Pilosity short, decumbent, abundant. Midtibiae with teeth (
<figureCitation box="[960,1060,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–296" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetId="figure-252@72.[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 292–296. L. unicolor. Male. 292, Head and pronotum; 293, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) and pad (Fos); 294, Midtibia showing the row of teeth (Te); 295, Hemelytron showing the stub (Stu) in membranae; 296, Scheme of pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947977/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 293</figureCitation>
), similar to foretibiae (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1424,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–296" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetId="figure-252@72.[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 292–296. L. unicolor. Male. 292, Head and pronotum; 293, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) and pad (Fos); 294, Midtibia showing the row of teeth (Te); 295, Hemelytron showing the stub (Stu) in membranae; 296, Scheme of pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947977/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 294</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: Hairs on dorsal surface of abdomen short, sparse. Genitalia: Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1198,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 292–296" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetId="figure-252@72.[340,1247,375,1438]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 292–296. L. unicolor. Male. 292, Head and pronotum; 293, Foretibia showing the row of teeth (Te) and pad (Fos); 294, Midtibia showing the row of teeth (Te); 295, Hemelytron showing the stub (Stu) in membranae; 296, Scheme of pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947977/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 296</figureCitation>
) with right paramere vestigial; left paramere more than half the width of pygophore and distally acute. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1070,1166,295,320]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Female:</emphasis>
More robust than male, similarly colored. Head: Proportion of antennal segments (I:II:III:IV) 1: 3.2: 2.4: 2.4. Thorax: Pronotum with sides not sinuate, carina more marked than in male and calli more flattened.
</paragraph>
